'''Audrey Samson''' is a Canadian a multidisciplinary artist-researcher whose work points to the materiality of data and its consequences.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://thelinknewspaper.ca/article/putting-data-to-rest|title=Putting Data to Rest &#124; Fringe Arts – The Link|date=2015-03-03|website=Thelinknewspaper.ca|accessdate=2016-04-03}}</ref> She is largely known for her exploration of erasure as a means of knowledge production through digital data funerals.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://diereferentin.servus.at/die-schmutzigen-seiten-unserer-high-tech-welt/|title=Die Referentin;Die schmutzigen Seiten unserer High Tech Welt|website=diereferentin.servus.at|accessdate=2017-06-08}}</ref>
Samson studied Media Design at the [[Piet Zwart Institute]], where she obtained a MFA in 2007.
Together with Sabrina Basten, she co-founded Roger10-4.<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=https://roger10-4.hotglue.me/ |title=Roger10-4 |language=en |accessdate=21 August 2017}}</ref> Their work was featured in ''[[Arte]]'',<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://creative.arte.tv/de/episode/leaking-transmediale-medienkunst-zeiten-totaler-transparenz |title=Leaking Transmediale: Medienkunst in Zeiten totaler Transparenz &#124; ARTE Creative |language=de |website=Creative.arte.tv |date= |accessdate=2016-04-03}}</ref> [[NRK]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nrk.no/nett-tv/indeks/287047/ |archive-url=https://archive.is/20160403021735/http://www.nrk.no/nett-tv/indeks/287047/ |dead-url=yes |archive-date=2016-04-03 |title=NRK Nett-TV - hastighetsmåling |website=Nrk.no |date= |accessdate=2016-04-03}}</ref> and Motherboard. She has been an active member of the networked performance group aether9,<ref>{{Cite book|title=aether9 - Remote Realtime Storytelling|last=aether9|first=|publisher=Greyscale Press|year=2011|isbn=978-2-9700706-4-1|location=Ghent|pages=}}</ref> and the feminist tech network Genderchangers. Samson is also known by the pseudonym ideacritik, and is part of the duo FRAUD.<ref>{{cite web|author=Somerset House Studios |url=https://www.somersethouse.org.uk/residents/fraud |title=Somerset House Studios residents |language=en |accessdate=21 August 2017}}</ref>
