'''''Barnaviridae''''' is a family of [[viruses]]. Cultivated [[mushroom]] serve as natural hosts. There are currently only one genus (''Barnavirus'') and one species in this family: the type species ''Mushroom bacilliform virus''. Diseases associated with this family include: [[Mycovirus#History|La France disease]].<ref name=ViralZone>{{cite web|title=Viral Zone|url=http://viralzone.expasy.org/all_by_species/177.html|publisher=ExPASy|accessdate=12 June 2015}}</ref><ref name=ICTV>{{cite web|last1=ICTV|title=Virus Taxonomy: 2014 Release|url=http://ictvonline.org/virusTaxonomy.asp|accessdate=12 June 2015}}</ref>

