{{Infobox journal | title = The Musical Times | cover = | editor = | discipline = [[Classical music]] | abbreviation = | formernames = The Musical Times and Singing Class Circular | publisher = Musical Times Publications | country = United Kingdom | frequency = Quarterly | history = 1844–present | openaccess = | license = | impact = | impact-year = | website = | link1 = | link1-name = | link2 = | link2-name = | JSTOR = 00274666 | OCLC = 53165808 | LCCN = 2004-235602 | CODEN = | ISSN = 0027-4666 | eISSN = }} '''''The Musical Times''''' is an [[academic journal]] of [[classical music]] edited and produced in the [[United Kingdom]] and currently the oldest such journal still being published in that country. It was originally published as '''''The Musical Times and Singing Class Circular''''' from 1844 until 1903.<ref>[https://www.jstor.org/publisher/mtpl Publisher Information: Musical Times Publications Ltd]. Retrieved 9 August 2009.</ref><ref>[https://www.jstor.org/stable/904250?seq=1 "Front Matter"]. ''The Musical Times and Singing Class Circular'', 1 December 1903, Vol. 44, No. 730. {{JSTOR|904250}}.</ref> Its title was shortened to its present name from January 1904.<ref>[https://www.jstor.org/stable/903288?seq=1 "Front Matter"]. ''The Musical Times'', January–December 1904, Volume XLV. {{JSTOR|903288}}.</ref> The journal originally appeared monthly but is now a quarterly publication. It is also available online at [[JSTOR]] and [[RILM]] Abstracts of Music Literature Full Text.
Past editors include F. G. Edwards (1897&ndash;1909),<ref>{{cite wikisource | class = journal | wslink = The Musical Times/Vol. 51 | plaintitle = The Musical Times | chapter = Frederick George Edwards | volume = 51 | issue = 803 | year = January 1910 | pages = 9–11}}</ref> [[Harvey Grace]], [[Stanley Sadie]] (1967&ndash;1987) and Eric Wen.
